The paper deals with data compression and similarity queries, which are topics that are commonly studied in information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the tradeoff between compression rate and query reliability, which is a topic that falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and cryptography (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper uses convex programming to evaluate the minimal compression rate, which is a technique commonly used in optimization and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
